import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About & Methodology | SpykeVision"
  description="Who's behind SpykeVision and how every projector is measured."
  active="about"
>
  <main class="wrap">
    <div class="article-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 style="text-align:center">Independent reviews, transparent methodology.</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>SpykeVision is an independent, reader-supported home-theater publication. I review projectors the way I'd want them reviewed: with real measurements, full transparency about test conditions, and no marketing spin. If a number looks too good, I tell you why, and how I measured it.</p>

      <h2>How I measure</h2>
      <p>Every review is built on a consistent bench process so results are comparable across products:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Brightness:</strong> measured in calibrated picture modes (not the brightest factory preset), across the full zoom and aperture range, after thermal stabilization.</li>
        <li><strong>Native contrast:</strong> full-field on/off, per zoom and aperture position.</li>
        <li><strong>ANSI contrast:</strong> 8×8 pattern, measured at both centered and shifted lens positions.</li>
        <li><strong>ADL contrast:</strong> across content levels from on/off through 50% ADL.</li>
        <li><strong>Optics:</strong> sharpness patterns, distortion via laser level, uniformity maps, and lens-shift behavior.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note"><strong>Transparency first:</strong> if you want to reproduce a measurement, the test pattern, meter and conditions are documented alongside each chart. Spotted something off? Get in touch; corrections are published openly.</div>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>Reviews also appear on the <a href="https://www.avsforum.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AVS Forum</a>, where discussion is always welcome. For review requests, corrections or manufacturer inquiries, reach out via the forum or the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
